@hostAddress = http://localhost:5184
@auth_token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@admin_token = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Server API Tests
### Instructions:
### 1. First run the login request in test-auth.http to get JWT tokens
### 2. Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with actual tokens from login response
### 3. Base URL: {{hostAddress}}

### Health Check (if implemented)
# GET {{hostAddress}}/api/health

### Products API Tests

### 1. Get All Products
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 2. Get Product by ID
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 3. Create New Product
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "code": "TEST001",
  "name": "Test Product",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 100,
  "location": "Warehouse A"
}

### 4. Update Product
PUT {{hostAddress}}/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "id": 1,
  "code": "TEST001",
  "name": "Updated Test Product",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 150,
  "location": "Warehouse B"
}

### 5. Delete Product
DELETE {{hostAddress}}/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### Inventory API Tests

### 6. Get Inventory Movements
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/inventory
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### 7. Record Inventory Movement
POST {{hostAddress}}/api/inventory/movement
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

{
  "productId": 1,
  "movementType": "In",
  "quantity": 50
}

### 8. Get Low Stock Products
GET {{hostAddress}}/api/inventory/low-stock
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

